  "text": "Using the estimated volume of bleeding as a determinant of RBCT has two drawbacks: on the one hand, it is often difficult to determine and, in fact, at least in specific surgeries, the actual blood loss can be almost double that observed [CITATION_1] . Also, the effects of bleeding will depend on factors such as the previous Hb, the circulating volume for the individual (which, in turn, depends on weight, height and sex), the rate of bleeding or the quality of volume replacement.",
